<topic id='element_referring_organisation_code.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: REFERRING ORGANISATION CODE - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_referring_organisation_code">REFERRING ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
 is the same as attribute 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODE</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_referring_organisation_code">REFERRING ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
 is the 
              <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_organisation_code">ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
 of the 
              <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_organisation">ORGANISATION</xref>
 from which the referral is made, such as a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_gp_practice">GP Practice</xref>, 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_nhs_trust">NHS Trust</xref>
 or 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_nhs_foundation_trust">NHS Foundation Trust</xref>.        </p>
      <p>This information is essential for managing service agreements which are based on patterns of referral.</p>
      <p>
         <b>
            <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_referring_organisation_code">REFERRING ORGANISATION CODE</xref>
 will be replaced with 
                  <xref outputclass="element"
                  keyref="element_organisation_identifier__referring_">ORGANISATION IDENTIFIER (REFERRING)</xref>, when it has been approved for use in national information standards.            </b>
      </p>
  </div>
